title: Kevin McAuliffe Police Records (Las Vegas Metropolitan Police Department)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Nevada Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any files, court documents, and court minutes related to the 2011-2012 arrest and sentencing of Monsignor Kevin McAuliffe, formerly a priest at St. Elizabeth Ann Seton Catholic School in Las Vegas, Nevada.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Natalie Katsaros

title: Chicago Cubs/White Sox and Public Health | Air Quality (Chicago Department of Public Health)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

1)All external correspondence, including email, phone, fax, or video (i.e., Google Meet/Hangouts, Zoom, etc.) between the Chicago Cubs and Chicago White Sox and your department referencing air quality in Chicago.
2) All external correspondence, including email, phone, fax, or video, between Major League Baseball (MLB) and your department referencing air quality in Chicago.
3) All external correspondence, including email, phone, fax, or video, between the Major League Baseball Player's Association (MLBPA) and your department regarding air quality in Chicago.
4) All internal correspondence (including email, phone, fax, or video) regarding the Cubs, White Sox, MLB, and/or MLBPA.

Between the dates 06/04/23- 06/30/23

If you determine that any information qualifies for an exemption from disclosure, I ask you to note whether the exemption is discretionary and, if so, whether it is necessary in this case to exercise your discretion to withhold the information.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge and processed by a representative of the news media/press and is made in the process of news gathering and not for commercial usage.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I also ask that our request be filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available (email: holler@bwd.nyc) – if not, secure file transfer, thumb drive, or CD-ROM. I am also available via phone at 718.360.6359 to discuss any questions you have about the request.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Bradford William Davis
